WEBVTT

01:28.881 --> 01:31.716
I'll tell you a secret.
We could be more profitable.

01:31.800 --> 01:32.759
Small places here and there,

01:32.843 --> 01:35.094
we could make more money.
You know why we don't?

01:35.179 --> 01:36.554
We choose not to.

01:36.638 --> 01:37.889
It's a hell of a business plan, Reese.

01:37.973 --> 01:39.766
Have a seat if you want.

01:39.850 --> 01:41.809
There's coffee and juice over there.

01:41.894 --> 01:43.102
How did you find out?

01:43.187 --> 01:45.563
We didn't find out. We figured it out.
That's an important distinction.

01:45.647 --> 01:48.065
We could have found out by you telling us.

01:48.150 --> 01:49.817
But Sloan Sabbith figured it out

01:49.902 --> 01:51.944
when instead of going down
off a weak earnings report,

01:52.488 --> 01:56.532
our stock traded up because someone
was buying 5% of our shares.

01:56.617 --> 01:58.618
-6%.
-6%.

01:58.702 --> 02:02.371
Which, when added to the 45%
that vests when you turn 25,

02:02.456 --> 02:04.290
comes out to a total of what, Randy?

02:04.374 --> 02:06.209
King Arthur's knights
could have jousted on this table.

02:06.293 --> 02:08.127
51 %, that's right.

02:08.212 --> 02:09.796
Please don't give my brother a math quiz.

02:09.880 --> 02:11.172
I wasn't testing his math.

02:11.256 --> 02:12.882
I was testing his attention span.

02:12.966 --> 02:15.301
-Reese. You're a douche.
-Yeah? Yes, I am.

02:15.385 --> 02:17.303
But I'm a douche on the side of the angels.

02:17.387 --> 02:19.639
And the reason there are areas,
small places here and there

02:19.723 --> 02:21.849
where we choose not to be more profitable

02:22.226 --> 02:24.769
is because we define success
a little different than you do.

02:25.354 --> 02:28.439
For instance, we have a news division.

02:32.569 --> 02:34.070
- Are you nervous?
- No.

02:35.113 --> 02:36.113
Really?

02:36.198 --> 02:37.406
-I'm okay.
-Mmm.

02:38.617 --> 02:40.159
-I'd be nervous.
-I'm fine.

02:40.244 --> 02:41.410
-Here she comes.
-Yeah.

02:41.495 --> 02:42.578
-Don't be nervous.
-I'm not.

02:43.413 --> 02:47.166
I would love it if you guys
would stop committing federal crimes.

02:47.251 --> 02:49.001
Listen, we're a team here. We're a family.

02:49.086 --> 02:50.586
But just to be clear, he's the one who did it.

02:51.505 --> 02:52.880
Before we start, Neal,

02:53.257 --> 02:55.842
it's very important that
you don't reveal your source to me.

02:55.926 --> 02:56.926
Yeah, no, I won't.

02:57.261 --> 02:58.636
If you were to reveal your source

02:58.720 --> 03:00.596
and then even in the course
of an informal conversation

03:00.681 --> 03:03.683
told me you were planning on continuing
to commit this very serious felony,

03:04.184 --> 03:06.394
attorney-client privilege
wouldn't protect either one of us.

03:06.645 --> 03:07.645
He's been prepped.

03:08.021 --> 03:09.021
By whom?

03:09.439 --> 03:12.358
By a member of the New York bar
who graduated seventh in his class

03:12.442 --> 03:14.235
from the fourth best law school in America.

03:14.319 --> 03:15.361
Okay.

03:16.029 --> 03:19.448
Well, as a member of the New York,
California, Illinois, and Florida bars

03:19.533 --> 03:22.535
who graduated second in her class
from the third best law school in the world,

03:22.870 --> 03:24.912
you won't mind if I sweep up after you a little?

03:24.997 --> 03:30.001
Because this is different than prosecuting
an escort service in Greenpoint.

03:30.085 --> 03:33.296
I put away bad guys, Halliday.
I locked up Mafia dons.

03:33.463 --> 03:36.465
And now when you go to work,
you put on makeup, just like me.

03:36.925 --> 03:38.217
Say you want another lawyer.

03:38.302 --> 03:40.970
If it's gonna be like this,
I'd honestly prefer to go to jail.

03:41.638 --> 03:42.722
When they were just your age,

03:42.806 --> 03:46.267
my mother's parents saw a production of
You Can't Take It With You on Broadway.

03:47.769 --> 03:50.396
They thought it was a shame
that you had to live near New York

03:50.480 --> 03:53.274
or be able to afford to come here
on vacation to see a production that good.

03:53.859 --> 03:55.526
So they went to investors

03:56.111 --> 04:00.114
and they put together $42,350

04:00.198 --> 04:01.616
and mounted a touring company.

04:02.910 --> 04:05.912
National Theatricals became very successful.

04:05.996 --> 04:09.874
And my mother worked in the office
while she was going to City College.

04:09.958 --> 04:12.376
She discovered a small string
of radio stations

04:12.461 --> 04:14.045
that were going out of business,

04:14.129 --> 04:16.839
and using National as collateral,

04:16.965 --> 04:19.342
she got a loan and bought
the company that owned them,

04:19.426 --> 04:21.385
which was named after a mythical city,

04:22.429 --> 04:23.888
Atlantis Media.

04:25.057 --> 04:27.642
She was 22 years old at the time.

04:28.226 --> 04:30.436
She met our father

04:30.520 --> 04:31.979
and they got married.

04:32.064 --> 04:33.397
And then she had a son

04:33.482 --> 04:36.192
who bore a striking resemblance
to the father's brother.

04:36.652 --> 04:39.487
If we're gonna start at 212 degrees,
we've got no place to go.

04:40.572 --> 04:43.240
In the divorce, she gave him half
the controlling shares of the company,

04:43.325 --> 04:44.784
or 45%.

04:44.868 --> 04:46.786
With another 45% going to you.

04:46.870 --> 04:49.246
- I own no stock in AWM.
- In your mother's will.

04:49.331 --> 04:50.289
I don't know what's in my mother's will.

04:50.374 --> 04:51.374
I don't like to think about it.

04:51.458 --> 04:52.625
You know exactly what's
in your mother's will.

04:52.709 --> 04:54.877
Is this what this is? Is this a family feud?

04:56.380 --> 04:59.173
'Cause we're not talking about
Elton John's birthday party now.

04:59.257 --> 05:00.341
Lives are on the line.

05:00.425 --> 05:03.678
Do me a favor and talk to me
with a little more condescension.

05:03.762 --> 05:05.346
Great day in the morning.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.682
Randy and Blair are in the house.

05:07.766 --> 05:08.808
Morning.

05:08.892 --> 05:11.894
Did you know I've known these two
since the minute they were born?

05:11.979 --> 05:15.398
Your father's plane was grounded in the snow

05:15.482 --> 05:17.984
and he called me from a pay phone and said,

05:18.068 --> 05:20.736
"Charlie, get yourself
to Columbia Presbyterian.

05:20.821 --> 05:24.031
"Monica's in labor and I want to
make sure nobody steals my kids."

05:24.825 --> 05:27.785
I wasn't in the delivery room,
'cause, you know, boundaries.

05:27.869 --> 05:31.747
But we're all family here, is my point.

05:32.249 --> 05:34.208
Randy, you're an absolute knockout.

05:34.292 --> 05:36.961
And, Blair, you've grown
into a fine young man.

05:37.337 --> 05:39.046
I'm Blair. He's Randy.

05:39.881 --> 05:42.091
All right, well, that was bound to happen.

05:42.175 --> 05:44.510
Look, I don't get involved
at the corporate level.

05:44.970 --> 05:46.721
I just came in to say hello.

05:46.805 --> 05:48.139
I'm not even sitting down.

05:48.223 --> 05:50.307
But out of curiosity,

05:50.392 --> 05:52.518
if you were to sell the company,

05:52.602 --> 05:56.313
what would the new owners'
plans be for ACN?

05:56.773 --> 05:58.107
I really don't know, Charlie,

05:58.191 --> 06:00.526
but from what I understand,
you can make more money

06:00.610 --> 06:03.362
selling the cameras than
transmitting images from them.

06:03.447 --> 06:05.740
So, I imagine that's what they'll do.

06:06.825 --> 06:08.659
Yeah, I'm gonna sit down.

06:09.578 --> 06:11.662
Let's start at the beginning. Monday night.

06:11.872 --> 06:12.872
Go ahead.

06:12.956 --> 06:14.457
You don't have to tell him to go ahead,
I just did.

06:14.541 --> 06:16.917
And I was telling him
it was okay to follow your instruction.

06:17.002 --> 06:18.002
Go ahead.

06:19.296 --> 06:20.713
It was the first night of the Boston story

06:20.797 --> 06:23.299
and I got a message on the site
asking for my encryption key.

06:23.383 --> 06:24.425
I gave it.

06:24.509 --> 06:26.969
Then I was asked for a higher level
of encryption and I gave that.

06:27.304 --> 06:29.638
The source instructed me
to buy an air-gapped computer,

06:29.723 --> 06:31.724
a computer that's never been
hooked up to the Internet.

06:31.808 --> 06:33.684
And he told me where
he had hidden the flash drive.

06:33.769 --> 06:36.103
It was hidden Godfather-style
in a restaurant bathroom.

06:36.188 --> 06:37.188
Godfather-style?

06:37.272 --> 06:39.231
The scene where Michael shoots
Barzini and the cop.

06:39.316 --> 06:40.399
-McCluskey.
-Right.

06:40.484 --> 06:42.443
- And it was Sollozzo.
- The cop?

06:42.527 --> 06:43.527
The cop was McCluskey.

06:43.612 --> 06:45.613
It was McCluskey and Sollozzo, not Barzini.

06:45.697 --> 06:47.281
-Maybe we can move past this.
-You got the flash drive...

06:47.365 --> 06:48.741
And loaded it onto the air-gapped computer.

06:48.825 --> 06:50.409
And what was on the drive?

06:50.494 --> 06:53.996
A little more than 27,000 documents
belonging to the DOD.

06:54.081 --> 06:55.164
About half of them classified.

06:55.248 --> 06:56.499
Tell her about Kundu.

06:56.583 --> 06:59.752
There's a small African country
called the Republic of Equatorial Kundu.

06:59.836 --> 07:00.920
It's a failed state.

07:01.004 --> 07:03.964
The week before last,
there were violent riots that killed 38 people,

07:04.049 --> 07:05.341
including three Americans.

07:06.802 --> 07:08.219
We're the ones who started the riots.

07:08.303 --> 07:09.428
How?

07:09.513 --> 07:12.014
The Pentagon employs a PR firm
in Virginia called BCD.

07:12.182 --> 07:13.599
They do propaganda work

07:13.683 --> 07:16.644
planting positive stories
about the US in local papers.

07:16.728 --> 07:19.271
But this time, they planted a story in Kundu

07:19.356 --> 07:22.191
about a rebel leader
who was about to attack another rebel group.

07:22.275 --> 07:24.693
The story was false
and now 38 people are dead.

07:25.028 --> 07:27.988
In order to be able to better convince
Charlie to spend the money

07:28.073 --> 07:30.407
on investigators to go
through the 27,000 documents,

07:30.492 --> 07:33.661
I asked the source to get me
a couple of pieces of persuasive evidence,

07:33.745 --> 07:35.663
-and I taught him how to use the NIPRNet...
-Yeah.

07:35.747 --> 07:37.706
...to move it from
the DOD's computer to mine.

07:37.791 --> 07:38.791
You were aware these were

07:38.875 --> 07:40.126
- stolen documents?
- Yes.

07:40.210 --> 07:41.210
And you asked your source

07:41.294 --> 07:42.419
-to steal some more?
-Yes.

07:42.504 --> 07:44.088
You even taught him how to do it?

07:44.714 --> 07:45.798
Yeah.

07:45.882 --> 07:47.466
Well, here's what you've done.

07:48.844 --> 07:51.262
You've committed espionage.

07:52.139 --> 07:54.932
You violated Title 18, Section 793.

07:55.016 --> 07:58.185
Aside from the Espionage Act,
you can and will be charged with violating

07:58.270 --> 08:01.814
the Computer Fraud and Abuse Act,
as well as federal statutes

08:01.898 --> 08:05.192
that punish the theft or retention of stolen...

08:05.277 --> 08:07.069
I mean, I know these guys get legal training.

08:07.154 --> 08:08.654
How does this happen?

08:08.780 --> 08:10.489
Isn't this the very first thing
they're taught not to do?

08:10.574 --> 08:12.032
-Once a year.
-Like, is there a sign hanging somewhere?

08:12.117 --> 08:13.409
It's not like they take
a semester of criminal law.

08:13.493 --> 08:14.493
Like a choking hazard sign?

08:14.578 --> 08:17.913
"Don't ask sources to steal things for you."

08:18.415 --> 08:20.499
Title 18, 641.

08:20.584 --> 08:22.793
Title 18, 793-E.

08:22.878 --> 08:24.837
18, 1030-a.

08:24.921 --> 08:26.964
And you violated the USA Patriot Act.

08:27.048 --> 08:29.341
Seems like the US government
has an awful lot of laws

08:29.426 --> 08:30.885
protecting itself from its citizens.

08:30.969 --> 08:33.470
That's one way of looking at it.
It's a stupid way.

08:33.555 --> 08:35.055
Is the DOD aware of this yet?

08:35.140 --> 08:38.601
No, but if we were to run the story,
which we obviously won't,

08:38.685 --> 08:41.645
we'd pick up the phone and find someone
at BCD to talk to on a Saturday.

08:41.730 --> 08:42.688
Once we did that...

08:42.772 --> 08:45.774
It would take about 10 seconds for BCD
to alert the Defense Department

08:45.859 --> 08:47.818
and the FBI would show up here in an hour.

08:47.903 --> 08:49.361
And they would take you in for questioning

08:49.446 --> 08:51.197
and not let you go
until you reveal your source.

08:51.281 --> 08:52.281
That's not gonna happen.

08:52.365 --> 08:54.283
Not gonna happen 'cause
we're not gonna run the story.

08:54.367 --> 08:56.785
We are gonna run the story
and I will avail myself

08:56.870 --> 08:59.872
of the protection the First Amendment gives
me when it comes to revealing a source.

08:59.956 --> 09:01.582
Neither the First nor any other
amendment protects you

09:01.666 --> 09:03.459
when you conspire to commit treason.

09:04.002 --> 09:06.212
Don't run the story
and you don't have to call BCD.

09:06.296 --> 09:08.380
Don't call BCD and nobody knows
you have the documents.

09:08.465 --> 09:10.549
Don't ever make contact
with your source again.

09:10.634 --> 09:14.094
A truth that matters can't stay hidden
and it's no more complicated than that.

09:14.179 --> 09:17.723
It's a lot more complicated than that,
and I decide what goes on the air.

09:17.807 --> 09:20.976
So, in point of fact,
we'll be doing exactly what Rebecca just said,

09:21.061 --> 09:22.937
which is to say nothing.

09:42.165 --> 09:43.207
Look at that.

09:43.750 --> 09:45.918
Is that a good enough score
to get me in the FBI?

09:46.002 --> 09:48.003
It's not a good enough score
to get you in the PTA.

09:48.338 --> 09:50.422
I put two shots right in the torso.

09:51.007 --> 09:53.842
Unfortunately, the other four hit
anyone standing next to the torso.

09:55.053 --> 09:56.845
Hey. Thanks.

09:56.972 --> 09:58.097
Thank you.

10:03.144 --> 10:04.186
That one's yours?

10:04.854 --> 10:07.022
It belongs to the Bureau, but, yeah.

10:07.107 --> 10:08.691
Tell me something.
Why don't they allow people

10:08.775 --> 10:10.276
to go in there alone?

10:10.360 --> 10:12.486
They don't want to make it
easier to commit suicide.

10:14.197 --> 10:15.698
So these are the good people with the guns

10:15.782 --> 10:17.866
who are going to stop
the bad people with the guns.

10:18.368 --> 10:19.910
- We're the good people with the guns.

10:20.537 --> 10:22.288
How's the wedding coming along?

10:22.372 --> 10:26.375
Be easier if people stopped
detonating bombs in Boston

10:26.459 --> 10:28.961
and factories stopped blowing up in Texas.

10:29.254 --> 10:30.671
I missed a fitting last week.

10:30.755 --> 10:32.548
- Casualty count keeps rising.

10:33.425 --> 10:36.302
-I need to ask you about something.
-I figured.

10:36.386 --> 10:38.637
-It'll be hypothetical.
-It needs to be.

10:38.722 --> 10:40.806
They give us a polygraph test every five years

10:40.890 --> 10:42.057
and mine's coming up.

10:42.809 --> 10:45.311
In today's climate,
what happens to a reporter

10:45.395 --> 10:48.188
who's made contact
with a government whistle-blower?

10:48.273 --> 10:50.482
-A leaker.
-A whistle-blower.

10:50.567 --> 10:53.444
A leaker of secrets
who has taken it upon himself

10:53.528 --> 10:55.571
to decide what laws to obey.

10:56.239 --> 10:58.324
A reporter might gain
the favor of the government

10:58.408 --> 11:02.036
by reporting such a leak to us
instead of the general public.

11:02.120 --> 11:04.705
That reporter's organization
would never have another source again.

11:04.789 --> 11:08.167
And one might say they'd abdicated
their responsibility to a democracy.

11:08.251 --> 11:09.918
Yeah, one might be full of shit, too.

11:11.421 --> 11:13.422
-Look, I...
-Nothing.

11:14.424 --> 11:16.175
The answer is nothing happens.

11:16.259 --> 11:19.178
No reporter's ever been prosecuted
under the Espionage Act.

11:19.304 --> 11:22.222
If they don't reveal their source,
they may be charged with contempt.

11:22.307 --> 11:24.683
And if they go to jail,
it's for an average of 10 days.

11:24.768 --> 11:26.101
At the most, it's been six months.

11:27.270 --> 11:29.146
- You sound disappointed, Molly.

11:29.230 --> 11:31.690
Sources come to us with things
they can't come to you with.

11:31.775 --> 11:33.859
Yeah, we have sources, too, Mac.

11:33.943 --> 11:35.944
We use them to stop
violent crimes before they happen.

11:36.363 --> 11:38.489
You want to protect your sources, so do we.

11:39.032 --> 11:40.741
'Cause when there's a leak,
our sources get executed.

11:46.081 --> 11:47.831
On most every occasion,
Obama refused to side

11:47.916 --> 11:50.334
with the EPA's more
science-based positions.

11:50.418 --> 11:53.545
I don't know, whether...
Whether it's cleaning up the air

11:53.630 --> 11:58.801
or forcing the national resources industries
to abide by existing regulations,

11:58.885 --> 12:04.390
ultimately the EPA is only as good
as the White House allows us to be.

12:04.474 --> 12:07.643
Okay, take the Deepwater Horizon oil spill.

12:08.978 --> 12:11.897
That was the largest oil spill
the US has experienced...

12:11.981 --> 12:14.274
Excuse me. Is this seat taken?

12:14.359 --> 12:15.359
No.

12:15.860 --> 12:17.986
Shh. Don't be alarmed, okay?

12:18.321 --> 12:19.321
Okay.

12:19.406 --> 12:22.199
I need a favor and I'll be able to
explain why in just a few minutes,

12:22.283 --> 12:24.326
but for now you have to trust a stranger.

12:24.411 --> 12:25.577
What's the favor?

12:25.662 --> 12:27.704
Hold my iPod and put in the earbuds.

12:27.956 --> 12:28.997
In your ears?

12:29.666 --> 12:31.542
In your ears like you're listening to it.

12:31.626 --> 12:32.876
You still have an iPod?

12:32.961 --> 12:34.128
I like the way the wheel clicks.

12:34.212 --> 12:35.712
But that's not important right now.

12:35.797 --> 12:37.214
-Will you do it?
-Yeah, sure.

12:37.549 --> 12:39.425
Well, I can give it to you on the record

12:39.509 --> 12:42.302
-or I can give it to you off the record.
-Shh.

12:42.387 --> 12:44.263
On the record is gonna make you laugh.

12:44.347 --> 12:45.681
On the record?

12:45.765 --> 12:50.394
The President continues
to believe in a strong EPA

12:50.478 --> 12:54.857
led by an advocate for smart
pro-growth environmental policies

12:54.941 --> 12:55.941
that will protect...

12:56.025 --> 12:59.361
Okay, now you're laughing
just as I said you would be.

12:59.446 --> 13:01.655
Off the record...

13:01.739 --> 13:03.031
Hey, hang on.

13:10.665 --> 13:15.335
Off the record, even he'd admit
he couldn't get a law through this Congress

13:15.670 --> 13:17.880
reaffirming the US
as the name of the country.

13:17.964 --> 13:21.341
So why bother wasting
what little capital he has

13:21.426 --> 13:22.426
with the Republicans on the Hill

13:22.510 --> 13:26.847
trying to get an up or down vote on his pick
to run a toothless agency?

13:28.057 --> 13:29.057
Mmm.

13:29.726 --> 13:31.310
I was gonna get the buffet.

13:31.394 --> 13:34.104
I don't know why, if given a choice,
anyone wouldn't get the buffet.

13:34.189 --> 13:35.898
Under what circumstance
would you order off the menu?

13:35.982 --> 13:37.441
If the menu had a 5-pound lobster

13:37.525 --> 13:39.818
and the buffet was soy-themed,
all-you-can-eat assorted soy.

13:39.903 --> 13:40.903
Here's what I need you to do.

13:40.987 --> 13:42.237
Why does there need to be an assignment?

13:42.322 --> 13:44.114
Hey, are we in this buffet thing together?

13:44.199 --> 13:46.408
Yeah, we tell the waiter
we're getting the buffet.

13:46.493 --> 13:48.702
I did a Q&A in Shape about my healthy diet.

13:48.786 --> 13:50.913
-You lied.
-In a big way and I'm really hungry.

13:50.997 --> 13:51.997
So I need you to get food for me

13:52.081 --> 13:53.207
-and I'll get food for you.
-Got it.

13:54.042 --> 13:56.335
Crab claws as far as the eye can see.

13:56.419 --> 13:57.878
Mushroom and Swiss cheese omelet.

13:57.962 --> 13:59.755
And I can't emphasize this enough...

13:59.839 --> 14:00.839
Waffles.

14:01.299 --> 14:03.258
-And what am I getting?
-Fruit salad.

14:03.927 --> 14:06.136
-Have you decided yet?
-We're gonna have the buffet.

14:06.262 --> 14:07.262
I'm only having something light,

14:07.347 --> 14:08.805
but I'm gonna keep him company
at the buffet.

14:08.932 --> 14:11.266
I know it seems like a waste
paying for the buffet and not eating it,

14:11.351 --> 14:12.434
but that's what I'm gonna do.

