43:14.509 --> 43:16.677
- The sex is good.
- Thank you.

43:17.512 --> 43:20.931
Invoking Leona Lansing
is gonna get you nowhere with me.

43:21.015 --> 43:22.766
Our fidelity is to our father's legacy,

43:22.850 --> 43:23.850
not his mother's.

43:23.977 --> 43:26.019
Then I can tell you this is not
what he would have wanted.

43:26.104 --> 43:27.771
-Then fuck him, too, Charlie.
-Hey!

43:27.855 --> 43:29.439
-All right.
-Why didn't our mother get shares?

43:29.524 --> 43:32.818
'Cause she's not the one that raised $42,350.

43:32.902 --> 43:34.528
She didn't build the company, she married it.

43:34.612 --> 43:36.029
Yeah, and like you poured the cement.

43:36.114 --> 43:37.781
As a matter of fact, with an MBA,

43:37.865 --> 43:39.866
he insisted on starting in the mail room.

43:39.951 --> 43:43.453
I understand we were born on third base,
but I'm stealing home now.

43:43.538 --> 43:45.706
-So that's about it.
-Shh.

43:46.040 --> 43:48.667
I'm not here.
I don't want to interrupt anything.

43:49.961 --> 43:51.086
Good afternoon, Leona.

43:51.504 --> 43:52.713
I'll tell you what.

43:52.797 --> 43:54.548
Leona is for friends and family.

43:54.632 --> 43:57.718
If you're trying to poach my company,
I'd prefer Mrs. Lansing.

44:00.305 --> 44:04.308
Oh, Blair, you get more beautiful
every time I see you.

44:04.392 --> 44:07.394
-How often is that?
-As infrequently as possible.

44:08.313 --> 44:10.814
I understand you've been
out on a date with Savannah Capital.

44:10.898 --> 44:12.357
And I let them take turns.

44:12.442 --> 44:15.110
And Randy, you like to watch, right?

44:15.820 --> 44:16.903
What?

44:17.947 --> 44:20.615
You know what happened last month
without anybody noticing?

44:20.700 --> 44:21.908
This is for real.

44:21.993 --> 44:26.288
Webster's Dictionary expanded
the definition of the word "literally"

44:26.372 --> 44:28.790
to include the way it's commonly misused.

44:28.875 --> 44:31.668
So the thing is, we no longer
have a word in the English language

44:31.753 --> 44:32.753
that means literally.

44:32.879 --> 44:34.796
I mean, literally doesn't have a synonym.

44:34.881 --> 44:37.382
So we're going to have to find
the Latin word for it and use it.

44:37.467 --> 44:39.176
But, see, I don't know any Latin.

44:39.260 --> 44:43.680
So when I say that I am literally gonna
set fire to this building with you in it

44:43.765 --> 44:45.891
before I hand over the keys to it,

44:45.975 --> 44:48.727
you don't know if I'm speaking
figuratively or literally.

44:49.270 --> 44:51.355
Savannah's offering $81 per share,

44:51.773 --> 44:54.608
so if this is about money,
you'll accept 82 from me, right?

44:54.692 --> 44:56.735
-Mom.
-We're not interested in selling 6%.

44:56.819 --> 44:59.780
I'm not interested in buying 6%!

44:59.864 --> 45:02.407
I don't want you anywhere near this company.

45:02.492 --> 45:03.492
I want all of it.

45:05.078 --> 45:08.663
I am offering you one full dollar per share
more than Savannah.

45:08.790 --> 45:10.916
So if this is about the money, you'll take it.

45:12.377 --> 45:13.585
$2.

45:15.755 --> 45:17.547
That's what I thought.

45:17.632 --> 45:20.717
I'll raise the cash and have an offer sheet
to you before your birthday.

45:21.636 --> 45:22.886
I tend to doubt it, but...

45:22.970 --> 45:25.764
Oh, get the fuck out of my boardroom, kids.

45:29.185 --> 45:30.394
Hey.

45:31.145 --> 45:32.896
How come we couldn't be friends, Blair?

45:32.980 --> 45:35.315
It's 'cause I can't stand you, Mrs. Lansing.

45:35.566 --> 45:37.484
You've got to lose that anger, honey.

45:38.194 --> 45:39.986
People get the face they deserve.

45:40.071 --> 45:41.238
See you in 10 days.

45:44.033 --> 45:45.117
Are you out of your mind?

45:45.201 --> 45:48.453
$4 billion for a $62 billion company?

45:48.538 --> 45:50.247
- It's a steal.
- It's not!

45:51.082 --> 45:52.499
But even if it were...

45:53.334 --> 45:55.377
- Yeah?
- I think he's trying to say

45:55.461 --> 45:57.629
you don't have $4 billion.

45:57.964 --> 45:59.131
-How much do I have?
-I don't know,

45:59.215 --> 46:03.343
but it's somewhere in the ballpark
of nothing close to $4 billion!

46:05.638 --> 46:07.097
Charlie, did I ever tell you about the time

46:07.181 --> 46:10.392
my parents saw
You Can't Take It With You on Broadway?

46:10.476 --> 46:12.394
That was $42,000.

46:12.478 --> 46:15.939
No, $42,350.

46:16.023 --> 46:19.443
And it was the last 350 that were the hardest.

46:19.527 --> 46:20.652
Sold my clothes,

46:20.736 --> 46:22.154
-dealt a little weed.
-Mom.

46:22.280 --> 46:24.281
Oh, I'm just kidding. I didn't sell my clothes.

46:24.365 --> 46:27.075
-This is for real.
-You think I don't fucking know that?

46:29.871 --> 46:32.372
I need $4 billion cash right now.

46:37.086 --> 46:38.295
I don't know who this guy is.

46:38.629 --> 46:40.839
I didn't vote for him.
I don't want him making decisions on his own

46:40.923 --> 46:41.965
about what's best for America.

46:42.049 --> 46:44.468
For all I know, he's one bad day away
from being Ted Kaczynski.

46:44.552 --> 46:48.054
We work with the FBI and the DOD
to determine what needs to be redacted.

46:48.139 --> 46:49.681
They're going to say
everything needs to be redacted.

46:49.765 --> 46:52.476
They know they have to convince me why.
And if I'm not sold...

46:52.560 --> 46:55.353
But just to get that far,
you have to call BCD, right?

46:55.438 --> 46:57.314
-To comment.
-That's it. That's the trip wire.

46:57.398 --> 46:59.691
You call BCD and Neal
has to give up his source

46:59.775 --> 47:00.942
or face a contempt charge.

47:01.027 --> 47:03.695
There's no route to the right
thing that doesn't include the possibility...

47:03.779 --> 47:05.947
The certainty
of a contempt charge.

47:06.032 --> 47:08.158
The route to the right thing
is this guy showing his face.

47:08.242 --> 47:10.535
Why is Neal paying the price
for this guy's patriotism?

47:10.620 --> 47:12.996
But we're past that.
And if I could switch places with him, I would.

47:13.080 --> 47:14.539
And I would
tell you the same thing,

47:14.624 --> 47:16.500
that a contempt charge could be the least...

47:16.584 --> 47:19.586
Too many people...
Look at how many people are in this room.

47:19.670 --> 47:21.421
They're in this room
'cause they can be trusted.

47:21.839 --> 47:25.008
Too many people already know that
a more serious crime has been committed.

47:25.092 --> 47:26.343
The FBI doesn't know that.

47:26.427 --> 47:27.636
- What if they find out?
- How?

47:27.720 --> 47:29.304
The only other person
who knows is the source,

47:29.388 --> 47:30.514
and he's not showing his face.

47:30.598 --> 47:32.098
- What if he does?
- He won't.

47:32.183 --> 47:33.433
So you completely trust a guy
who the only thing

47:33.518 --> 47:35.101
that we know about him
is that he stole

47:35.186 --> 47:36.561
classified documents
from the Department of Defense?

47:36.646 --> 47:38.688
We are three exits past that on the highway.

47:38.773 --> 47:40.690
I don't know why
this is a discussion.

47:40.775 --> 47:44.819
We obviously have to pursue this story
and we need to start right now.

47:45.947 --> 47:47.197
Wait here a second.

47:48.282 --> 47:51.660
Jenna, I want you to put
some menus on my desk.

47:51.744 --> 47:54.037
Three minutes after they get here,
I want you to come into my office

47:54.121 --> 47:55.789
and ask for the menus back.

47:55.873 --> 47:57.290
And that's it. You got it?

47:58.960 --> 48:00.710
-After who gets here?
-Trust me.

48:13.975 --> 48:16.309
In the time that you've been working here,
have you ever asked yourself

48:16.394 --> 48:18.728
why we always walk into
the studio through that door

48:18.813 --> 48:21.314
when we could just walk straight in
over that threshold?

48:21.399 --> 48:23.567
I did ask after I noticed it.

48:23.651 --> 48:25.235
What'd they say?

48:25.319 --> 48:27.487
-They said it was superstition.
-Huh.

48:28.155 --> 48:29.281
It's my superstition.

48:29.740 --> 48:33.493
Never asked anyone else to do it,
they just did.

48:33.578 --> 48:36.621
It's a longer walk.
I kind of feel responsible for that.

48:37.623 --> 48:39.666
You feel responsible for a lot of things.

48:40.876 --> 48:42.669
You already called BCD, right?

48:43.546 --> 48:45.130
A few hours ago
when you went to the bathroom,

48:45.214 --> 48:47.507
you were really calling BCD for comment.

48:48.676 --> 48:50.051
Yeah.

48:50.553 --> 48:52.095
You can do the story or not do the story,

48:52.179 --> 48:55.849
but now a decision can't be made
that considers my protection.

48:56.934 --> 48:58.685
I gave them my name.

49:01.731 --> 49:04.983
For a long time after you started here,
I didn't know your name.

49:06.611 --> 49:08.194
You called me Punjab.

49:10.114 --> 49:11.448
Yeah, you know, I...

49:12.450 --> 49:14.034
I sure know it now.

49:17.371 --> 49:18.705
Thank you.

49:19.415 --> 49:21.291
-Do something for me, would you?
-Sure.

49:21.375 --> 49:22.709
Give me the source.

49:23.919 --> 49:25.378
I need some skin in the game

49:25.463 --> 49:28.298
and they're gonna have
a trickier time of it with my profile.

49:28.382 --> 49:31.885
They'll need a day to figure out what to do
and negotiate with me and Rebecca.

49:31.969 --> 49:34.054
-Yeah, all right.
-One more thing.

49:34.138 --> 49:36.681
Do you have any place you can
get to for a day or two?

49:37.558 --> 49:38.558
It won't come to that.

49:38.643 --> 49:41.436
Someplace you can get to
without using a credit card.

49:42.563 --> 49:43.855
I can't tell if you're kidding.

49:43.939 --> 49:45.440
Leave your phone at home by accident.

49:45.524 --> 49:48.902
Greyhound doesn't need to know your name.
You know what I'm saying.

49:49.695 --> 49:51.279
It's just contempt.

49:51.405 --> 49:54.115
Why don't you go transcribe your notes
from the call to BCD

49:54.200 --> 49:56.159
and distribute them in the conference room?

50:00.081 --> 50:02.082
Neal Sampat.

50:08.881 --> 50:10.674
-Hello.
-We're on a break in there.

50:11.676 --> 50:13.385
Don and I are a couple.

50:13.469 --> 50:14.844
We've been seeing
each other for a few months.

50:14.929 --> 50:17.597
You can tell anybody you want
and you can use the word couple.

50:19.183 --> 50:20.183
Don, what's going on?

50:20.267 --> 50:21.851
-Yeah, don't worry about it.
-Okay.

50:26.148 --> 50:28.692
I would love to go to
your parents' made-up party.

50:28.776 --> 50:30.360
Are you just saying that
because it's made up?

50:30.444 --> 50:32.570
Because I would love
to go on a made-up hike with your cousins.

50:32.655 --> 50:33.863
No,

50:33.948 --> 50:35.949
I'm saying it because I'm in love with you.

50:39.704 --> 50:41.037
I love you, Don.

50:41.622 --> 50:43.665
You don't have to say anything back.

50:47.962 --> 50:48.962
Uh...

50:49.255 --> 50:50.255
Ha!

50:50.423 --> 50:51.798
Oh, shit!

50:52.133 --> 50:53.633
You have been tested
and you failed that test.

50:53.718 --> 50:54.884
I did not do well on that test.

50:54.969 --> 50:57.595
-You bit down hard.
-I failed that test.

50:58.222 --> 51:00.265
As long as you know that.

51:00.349 --> 51:01.808
Are you worried about getting scooped?

51:01.976 --> 51:03.226
-No.
-Yes.

51:03.310 --> 51:07.188
Because now I got to trust that somebody else
is going to handle the story responsibly.

51:07.273 --> 51:12.026
What if whoever the source goes to next
just makes a 27,000-page document dump?

51:12.111 --> 51:13.570
Nobody elected you either.

51:13.654 --> 51:16.406
I agree there's a kink in the system,
but look at me.

51:16.490 --> 51:19.576
Have you ever seen
a more trustworthy person in your life?

51:19.660 --> 51:20.994
I was born like this.

51:21.078 --> 51:23.663
By the way, how much money do you have?

51:24.457 --> 51:25.790
In the bank?

51:25.875 --> 51:28.251
Yeah, in an unrelated matter,

51:28.335 --> 51:33.423
Leona's gonna need, like, $4 billion
or this network's gonna be liquidated.

51:34.759 --> 51:37.302
-What was that?
-Don't worry about it right now.

51:48.063 --> 51:50.607
I'm Special Agent Hutchinson
and this is Special Agent Levy.

51:50.691 --> 51:52.901
We're with the FBI
and we need to question Neal Sampat.

51:52.985 --> 51:55.320
We also have a search warrant
under seal for your hard drives.

51:55.404 --> 51:56.529
Mac.

51:56.614 --> 51:58.490
I understand you two
know each other socially?

51:58.574 --> 52:00.617
I was telling Agent Hutchinson,

52:00.701 --> 52:02.786
I think we haven't seen
each other since Christmas.

52:02.870 --> 52:04.621
Yeah, that's right. It was, uh...

52:04.705 --> 52:07.457
It wasn't Christmas Eve,
it was the night before.

52:07.541 --> 52:09.751
I'm Charlie Skinner. I'm in charge.

52:09.835 --> 52:12.796
A warrant under seal means you're prohibited
from disclosing that you were served.

52:12.880 --> 52:14.964
-If you disclose that you were served...
-Agent Hutchinson, I'm...

52:15.049 --> 52:16.090
You're Rebecca Halliday.

52:16.175 --> 52:18.218
-You're the attorney for Mr. Sampat.
-Yeah.

52:19.678 --> 52:22.555
I represent ACN in First Amendment matters.

52:24.391 --> 52:27.560
You should answer your phone.
It's going to be the Attorney General.

52:30.231 --> 52:31.773
Rebecca Halliday.

52:31.857 --> 52:33.817
Which of you is Neal Sampat?

52:33.901 --> 52:35.652
Our lawyer has just stepped away.

52:35.736 --> 52:36.986
I have a warrant, Mr. Skinner.

52:37.071 --> 52:39.405
-Your lawyer knows...
-I'm Spartacus, sir.

52:39.532 --> 52:42.408
Neal's not in the room.
Why don't we go in my office for a minute?

52:43.619 --> 52:44.828
I want to talk to them alone.

52:44.912 --> 52:46.246
Prepare the search, but don't start.

52:47.414 --> 52:49.582
You know how many hard drives
we have in this place?

53:03.264 --> 53:04.681
Keep your voices very low.

53:04.765 --> 53:06.099
You didn't tell me it was this.

53:06.183 --> 53:09.018
I don't know what this is, Molly,
and I told you as little as possible.

53:09.103 --> 53:11.938
I have to say, raiding a newsroom
has got to be damn near unprecedented.

53:12.022 --> 53:13.398
We need to find this guy.

53:13.482 --> 53:14.524
This is a bad guy.

53:14.608 --> 53:15.859
We can't take your word for that.

53:15.943 --> 53:17.986
And as you well know,
bad guys are good sources.

53:18.070 --> 53:19.737
We want to work with you
on this story and we want...

53:19.822 --> 53:20.947
We want to work with you, too,

53:21.031 --> 53:22.782
but we're going to question Neal Sampat.

53:23.242 --> 53:24.868
The Attorney General is on the phone
telling your lawyer

53:24.952 --> 53:26.661
we're gonna hold him till he
gives up his source.

53:26.745 --> 53:28.538
And I'll tell you what else.

53:28.622 --> 53:30.999
There are three levels of Internet systems
the government works on.

53:31.083 --> 53:32.834
This guy was working on JWICS,

53:32.918 --> 53:36.337
and we don't believe he has the ability
to transfer content to the protocol router.

53:36.422 --> 53:39.799
So if we can prove your guy helped him do it,
he's getting charged with a full boat.

53:40.676 --> 53:42.468
He's going to Leavenworth.

53:42.636 --> 53:45.471
So if you want to work with us, let's start.

53:47.141 --> 53:48.391
-Excuse me.
-Yeah?

53:48.475 --> 53:50.768
- I just need your menu.
- Sorry.

53:50.853 --> 53:53.730
We're working through dinner tonight.

53:53.814 --> 53:55.607
Are we allowed to buy your guys dinner?

53:55.691 --> 53:56.691
No.

53:57.943 --> 53:59.027
Thanks.

54:00.821 --> 54:02.906
Molly, I know the name of the source, too.

54:05.075 --> 54:06.075
-You do?
-Yeah.

54:06.160 --> 54:07.577
-Who else?
-That's it.

54:10.414 --> 54:12.582
We need to start searching
your hard drives now.

54:12.666 --> 54:14.751
We won't talk anymore
till your lawyer's in the room.

54:26.472 --> 54:28.348
Excuse me. Excuse me.

54:30.851 --> 54:32.268
-What's going on?
-Welcome back.

54:33.520 --> 54:34.896
Sloan, what's going on?

54:35.022 --> 54:37.357
It's about Neal's story...

54:39.360 --> 54:40.485
Go ahead.

54:41.195 --> 54:42.946
Please step away from the desks.

54:43.989 --> 54:46.324
Could someone please tell me
where Neal Sampat works?

54:50.579 --> 54:52.038
He works over there.
